 <yangyifan@yangyifans-MacBook-Pro.local>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 11:09:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(verilog): vendor wasm grammar + register as Language
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1 Tasks 2-3 of kb_benchmark analyzer-v2.

WASM grammar built reproducibly via scripts/build-verilog-wasm.sh from
tree-sitter/tree-sitter-verilog@v1.0.3 (commit 521b535). The script
prefers emcc; falls back to docker build when emcc is unavailable.
Output is 17 MB — large vs other bundled grammars (5 MB max so far)
but unavoidable given tree-sitter-verilog's grammar size (~400 KB of
grammar.js compiled to ~85 KB parser.c via tree-sitter generate).

Registry edits (src/extraction/grammars.ts):
- WASM_GRAMMAR_FILES gains `verilog: 'tree-sitter-verilog.wasm'`
- EXTENSION_MAP gains .sv / .svh / .v / .vh -> verilog
- getLanguageDisplayName gains 'Verilog/SystemVerilog'

src/types.ts LANGUAGES tuple gains 'verilog' (placed between 'r' and
'yaml' to keep alphabetical-ish ordering).

`npm run build` succeeds with no TS errors. copy-assets picks up the
new .wasm via its existing readdirSync glob — nothing else to wire.
